UNSUPERVISED LEARNING - CLUSTERING
¶

Ricardo López Ruiz
¶

Date: 02/06/2021

Abstract:
¶

Different unsupervised learning techniques are used to identify different segments in the existing bank customers based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.

Techniques used in this project:
¶

'K-means' - 'Elbow curve' - 'Silhouette Score' - 'Clusters analysis'

¶

Project - Credit Card Customer Segmentation¶

Context:¶

You as a Data scientist forming part of the Operations team of the at AllLife bank wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customers queries are resolved faster.

Background:¶

AllLife Bank wants to focus on its credit card customer base in the next financial year. They have been advised by their marketing research team, that the penetration in the market can be improved. Based on this input, the Marketing team proposes to run personalised campaigns to target new customers as well as upsell to existing customers. Another insight from the market research was that the customers perceive the support services of the back poorly. Based on this, the Operations team wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customers queries are resolved faster. Head of Marketing and Head of Delivery both decide to reach out to the Data Science team for help.

Objective:¶

  • To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.
  • To answer the key questions:
    • How many different segments of customers are there?
    • How are these segments different from each other?
    • What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

Data Description:¶

  • Data is of various customers of a bank with their credit limit, the total number of credit cards the customer has, and different channels through which customer has contacted the bank for any queries, different channels include visiting the bank, online and through a call centre.

Index¶

  • Overview of the dataset

  • EDA

  • Business conclusion and Recomendations

In [26]:
clusters=range(1,11)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(data3)
    prediction=model.predict(data3)
    distortion=sum(np.min(cdist(data3, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / data3.shape[0]                       
    meanDistortions.append(distortion)
    print('Number of Clusters:', k, '\tAverage Distortion:', distortion)

plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method')

In [27]:
# Analysis with Silhoutte clustering 
sil_score = []
cluster_list = list(range(2,11))
for n_clusters in cluster_list:
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters)
    preds = clusterer.fit_predict((data3))
    #centers = clusterer.cluster_centers_
    score = silhouette_score(data3, preds)
    sil_score.append(score)
    print("For n_clusters = {}, silhouette score is {})".format(n_clusters, score))

plt.plot(cluster_list,sil_score)
plt.grid()

Clusters Comparison¶

  • Discussing cluster K-means clusters - Performing cluster profiling - Deriving Insights

Insights¶

  • Cluster 0:

    • This cluster contains costumers with medium credit (between 20000 and 50000), medium number of credit cards (between 4 and 6) and medium number of calls (between 1 and 3), minimum number of online visits (between 0 and 2) and maximum number of bank visits (between 3 and 5).

  • Cluster 1:

    • This cluster contains costumers with low credit (less than 20000), low number of credit cards (between 0 and 3) and low number of bank visits (between 0 and 2), medium number of online visits (between 2 and 4) and maximum number of calls (between 5 and 9).

  • Cluster 2:

    • This cluster contains costumers with maximum credit (more than 80000), maximum number of credit cards (between 8 and 10) and maximum number of online visists (more than 7), minimum number of calls (between 0 and 2) and minimum number of bank visits (between 0 and 1).

Business Conclusion and Recommendation¶

  • Business recommendations and insights

Business Recommendations¶

  • Cluster 0 consists of medium clients, with average credit and medium number of credit cards that they use to visit personally the bank offices before than to use the online methods. They can be an interesting target segment to increase the number of clients with credits and credit cards by using the personal information given presentially in offices.
  • Cluster 1 encloses the less profitable clients given that they take the lowest credits and the minimum number of credit cards. By other way, they use to call by phone before than using the personal visit to offices. Usually, they would not be the target for a campaign offering new credits or credit cards.
  • Cluster 2 is formed by the most risky and then profitable clients given that they take the greatest credits and the maximum number of credit cards. They use more the online methods before than the presential visit to offices. It is sure that they would be the main target segment for a campaign offering new credits or credit cards, better done by online methods.
